{{Infobox royalty | name = Prince Taima | native_name = 当麻皇子 | family_name & title = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | relation = Third [[Emperor Yōmei|son]] of the 31st [[Emperor Yōmei]] | title = | full_name = | Rank = | honorific = | emblem = | birth_date = [[Emperor Bidatsu]] 3 (c. [[574]]) – [[Emperor Yōmei]] 1 (c. [[586]]) | birth_place = | death_date = Unknown | death_place = | burial_date = | burial_place = | spouse1 = {{ill|Princess Toneri|ja|舎人皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Princess Toneri|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (daughter of [[:en:Emperor Kinmei|Emperor Kinmei]]) | spouse2 = | children = | father = [[:en:Emperor Yōmei|Emperor Yōmei]] (31st [[:en:Emperor of Japan|Emperor of Japan]]) | position = General of the Expedition to Silla (征新羅将軍) | religion = | signature = }}
Prince Taima (当麻皇子, たいま の みこ; born between '''Emperor Bidatsu 3''' (574?) and '''Emperor Yōmei 1''' (586?), date of death unknown) was a '''prince''' of the late '''Kofun period''' to the early '''Asuka period'''. He was also known as '''Prince Maroko (麻呂子皇子)'''. He was the '''third son of Emperor Yōmei'''. His descendants included the '''Taima clan (当麻氏)''', who became mid-level officials, and the '''Taima-Takada clan (当麻高田氏)''', a samurai family active in the '''Hirata estate (平田荘)''', centered around Yamato-Takada. He is also associated with the '''Oni-slaying legend of Ōeyama (大江山鬼退治伝説)'''.
== '''Career''' == In '''Suiko 10 (602)''', after his half-brother '''Prince Kurume (来目皇子)''', the Commander-in-Chief of the '''Expedition to Silla (征新羅大将軍)''', passed away, '''Prince Taima''' was appointed '''General of the Expedition to Silla (征新羅将軍)''' in '''Suiko 11 (603)'''.
He '''departed from Naniwa (難波) by ship''', but upon arriving in '''Akashi (明石), Harima Province (播磨国)''', his wife, '''Princess Toneri (舎人皇女)''', passed away. As a result, he '''buried her in Akashi''' and '''returned home'''.
== '''Lineage''' == * '''Father''': [[:en:Emperor Yōmei|Emperor Yōmei]] * '''Mother''': {{ill|Katsuragi Hiroko|ja|葛城広子|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsuragi Hiroko|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (daughter of '''Katsuragi Iwamura''' (葛城磐村))<ref name="shoki">『[[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]]』</ref><ref name="shou">『{{ill|Honchō kōin jōunroku|ja|本朝皇胤紹運録|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Honchō kōin jōunroku|qq=}}』</ref>, or '''Katsuragi Ihibiko no Iratsume''' (葛木伊比古郎女), daughter of '''Taimadera Kura-no-Muraji Hiriko (当麻倉首比里古)''' or '''Taimadera Kura-no-Hiko (当麻倉日子)'''.<ref name="kojiki">『[[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]]』</ref> * '''Wife''': {{ill|Princess Toneri|ja|舎人皇女|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Princess Toneri|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, daughter of [[:en:Emperor Kinmei|Emperor Kinmei]]
